  | Regarding the original problem described in [#24384 (comment)](https://github.com/containers/podman/discussions/24384#discussion-7377153)<br>It works when I add an addtional `UIDMap=0:999`<br>1. `sudo mkdir /srv/test`<br>2. `sudo chmod 1000:1000 /srv/test`<br>3. Create the file _/tmp/test.sh_ containing<br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   ```<br>   #!/bin/bash<br>   set -o errexit<br>   set -o nounset<br>   id=$1<br>   extraconf=$2<br>   cat << EOF > /etc/containers/systemd/${id}.container<br>   [Container]<br>   ContainerName=${id}<br>   Image=docker.io/library/alpine<br>   User=1000:1000<br>   UIDMap=1000:1000<br>   ${extraconf}<br>   Volume=/srv/test:/config:Z<br>   Exec=/bin/touch /config/${id}<br>   EOF<br>   <br>   systemctl daemon-reload<br>   systemctl start ${id}.service<br>   ls -ln /srv/test/${id}<br>   ```<br>   <br>4. Run command<br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   ```<br>   sudo bash /tmp/test.sh test1 ""<br>   ```<br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   The following output is printed<br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   ```<br>   Job for test1.service failed because the control process exited with error code.<br>   See "systemctl status test1.service" and "journalctl -xeu test1.service" for details.<br>   ```<br>   <br>5. Run command<br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   ```<br>   sudo bash /tmp/test.sh test2 "UIDMap=0:999"<br>   ```<br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   The following output is printed<br>   <br>   <br>   <br>   ```<br>   -rw-r--r--. 1 1000 1000 0 Oct 29 07:13 /srv/test/test2<br>   ``` |
  
